#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/installation-and-basic-configuration.xml:390
msgid "OTRS needs some additional Perl modules, as described in the Table 3-1. If you install OTRS from source, you'll have to install these modules manually. This can either be done with the package manager of your Linux distribution (<application>yast</application>, <application>apt-get</application>) or, like described in this section, through the Perl shell and CPAN. If you're using ActiveState Perl, for instance on Windows, you could use PPM, the built-in Perl Package Manager. If possible we advise you to use your package manager."
