#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:282
msgid "<ulink url=\"http://varlena.com/GeneralBits/Tidbits/annotated_conf_e.html\"> <citetitle>http://varlena.com/GeneralBits/Tidbits/annotated_conf_e.html</citetitle> </ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:291
msgid "If performance is still not satisfactory, we suggest that you join the PostgreSQL Performance mailing list ( <ulink url=\"http://www.postgresql.org/community/lists/\"> http://www.postgresql.org/community/lists/ </ulink> ) and ask questions there. The folks on the PostgreSQL list are very friendly and can probably help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:308
msgid "Of course you should use mod_perl 2.0 ( <ulink url=\"http://perl.apache.org/\"> <citetitle>http://perl.apache.org/</citetitle> </ulink>).  It's much faster (~ * 100) than pure cgi. But it needs more RAM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:316
msgid "Pre-establish database connections"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:318
msgid "You can have the database connections pre-established on startup of the web server.  This saves time (see README.webserver)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:324
msgid "Preloaded modules - startup.pl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:326
msgid "Use the startup script <filename>scripts/apache2-perl-startup.pl</filename> for preloaded/precompiled Perl modules on your mod_perl webserver to be faster and smaller (see README.webserver)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:331
msgid "Reload Perl modules when updated on disk"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:333
msgid "By default Apachee::Reload is used in scripts/apache2-httpd.include.conf. Disable it and you will get 8% more speed. But remember to restart the web server if you install any modules via the OTRS Package Manager, any values in your SysConfig or in Kernel/Config.pm.  Important: this would also mean you can't use the OTRS Package Manager via the web interface, you need to use the command line variant - <filename>bin/otrs.PackageManager.pl</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:343
msgid "Choosing the Right Strategy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:345
msgid "If you have a really large installation (over 1,000 new tickets per day and over 40 agents) it is a good idea to read \"Choosing the Right Strategy\" (<ulink url=\"http://perl.apache.org/docs/1.0/guide/strategy.html\"> <citetitle>http://perl.apache.org/docs/1.0/guide/strategy.html</citetitle> </ulink>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:354
msgid "mod_gzip/mod_deflate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/performance-tuning.xml:356
msgid "If your bandwidth is a little bit small, use mod_deflate for Apache2.  If you have an html page with 45k, mod_gzip/mod_deflate compresses it. The page will be about 7k. The drawback is that this increases load on the server side."
msgstr ""

